Race.SpecificTitle: PW Disabled Veterans -- Homestead Exemp. - PJ
Race.SummaryText: Parishwide Disabled Veterans Homestead Exemption Proposition
Race.FullText: Shall an additional homestead exemption be authorized in the Parish of Jackson, State of Louisiana, for certain disabled veterans and surviving spouses in accordance with and subject to the provisions of Article VII, Section 21(K) of the Louisiana Constitution, provided that this additional homestead exemption shall extend and apply to property in Jackson Parish only after approval by a majority of the registered voters of Jackson Parish voting on this proposition?

Race.SpecificTitle: PW Ambulance Service District -- 5.37 Mills Continuation - BOC - 10 Yrs.
Race.SummaryText:
Parishwide Ambulance Service District Proposition
(Millage Continuation)
Race.FullText: Shall the Jackson Parish Ambulance Service District, Jackson Parish, Louisiana (the "District"), be authorized to continue to levy a special tax of five and thirty-seven hundredths (5.37) mills on all property subject to taxation in the District (an estimated $1,210,000 reasonably expected at this time to be collected from the levy of the tax for an entire year), for a period of ten (10) years, beginning with the year 2019 and ending with the year 2028, to be dedicated and used for the purpose of maintaining and operating the District's ambulance service facilities and for purchasing ambulances and other ambulance service equipment, said millage to represent a sixty-two hundredths of a mill (.62) increase over the 4.75 mills tax authorized to be levied through the year 2018 pursuant to an election held on July 15, 2006?
